.TH _SIMPLE SHELL

.SH NAME
_SIMPLE SHELL - a simple UNIX command interpretor

.SH DESCRIPTION
The _simple_shell program behaves in the exact same way as the sh 
.br
The _simple_shell will display a prompt and wait for the user to type a command
.br
A command line always ends with a new line.
.br
The prompt is displayed again each time a command has been executed.
.br
The command lines can take arguments
.br
The first command will be considered as the command to be executed
.br
additional arguments will be considered as arguments to this first command
.br
the command will be searched for in the PATH
.br
the 'exit' command will exit the program
.br
If an executable cannot be found, an error message is printed and the prompt is displayed again.
.br
the 'env' command prints the actual environment

.SH AUTHOR
Written by Luke Holley-Boutillier <9972@holbertonstudents.com> & Korneel Loy <9795@holbertonstudents.com>
